al name referring to a house or inn distinguished by the sign of a lion. It is also found in Sweden. Compare   Loewe   1,   Lau  ,   Lave  , and   Lurvey  .","Jewish (Ashkenazic; <b>Löwe</b>): artificial name from German <i>Löwe</i> ‘lion’."]},{"name":"Leavitt","meanings":["English:","(of Norman origin): nickname from Anglo-Norman French <i>leuet</i> ‘wolf cub’ (see   Low   3).","habitational name from any of various places in Normandy called Livet. All are of obscure, presumably Gaulish, etymology."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Bright’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir John de Low was born in 1188, in Hatch, Somerset, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs Margery Low. He died about 1288, at the age of 101."},"et":{"1188–Abt 1288":"1188–umbes 1288","1194–Female":"1194–Surnud","1246–1310":"1246–1310","–Male":"Surnud","1188–1288":"1188–1288","1246":"1246","Abt 1288":"umbes 1288","1288":"1288","1310":"1310","1188":"1188","1194":"1194","Hatch, Somerset, England":"Hatch, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1188–Abt 1288":"1188–noin 1288","1194–Female":"1194–Kuollut","1246–1310":"1246–1310","–Male":"Kuollut","1188–1288":"1188–1288","1246":"1246","Abt 1288":"noin 1288","1288":"1288","1310":"1310","1188":"1188","1194":"1194","Hatch, Somerset, England":"Hatch, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1188–Abt 1288":"1188–environ 1288","1194–Female":"1194–Décédée","1246–1310":"1246–1310","–Male":"Décédé","1188–1288":"1188–1288","1246":"1246","Abt 1288":"environ 1288","1288":"1288","1310":"1310","1188":"1188","1194":"1194","Hatch, Somerset, England":"Hatch, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Sir John de Low est né en 1188, à Hatch, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a e